## Introduction

In this lab, we explore the concept of **One-Dimensional Arrays in C** and how loops are used to manipulate and process array data efficiently.

Arrays allow programmers to store multiple values of the same data type in a single variable, making it easier to manage and process large datasets. When combined with loops, arrays become powerful tools that enable efficient iteration, modification, and analysis of stored data.

Understanding arrays is essential in programming because they are widely used in data processing, record management, and algorithm implementation.

